    • Method Detail

      • getDistributions

        public static void getDistributions(int numWalks)
        The array "times" stores in each slot the amount of walks that took that many of steps to return. For instance, the amount of walks in numWalks that took 4 steps to return is stored in times[4]. The array "proportions" stores these proportions compared to the total number of walks.

      • getNumTimesReturned

        public static void getNumTimesReturned(int numWalks,
                                       int numSteps)
        The array "returned" stores in each slot the amount of walks that reached 0 that many times. For instance, the amount of walks in numWalks that took reached 0 four times is stored in returned[4]. The array "returnedProp" stores these proportions compared to the total number of walks.
